create desktop files for the /opt programs below and place them under
~/ins/system-opt-desktops
these files should get installed to /usr/local/share/applications/
via a new install script I should create (`install-system-opt-desktops`).
the install script should only install a desktop file if it detects the
executable is available on the system.

speedcrunch  # Calculator
darktable  # Virtual lighttable and darkroom for photos
doublecmd  # File Manager
ELECTRON_OZONE_PLATFORM_HINT=auto codium  # MS Visual Studio Code
foot bluetuith  # Bluetooth Manager
keymapp  # Moonlander Keyboard
googleearth  # Maps, GIS
